#. <section class="sutta" id="sn6.12"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn6.12:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 6"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 6"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn6.12:0.2"
msgid "2. Dutiyavagga"
msgstr "2. The Second Chapter"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn6.12:0.3"
msgid "12. Devadattasutta"
msgstr "12. About Devadatta"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts1ed" id="pts1ed1.154"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn6.12:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

msgctxt "sn6.12:1.2"
msgid ""
"ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati gijjhakūṭe pabbate acirapakkante "
"devadatte."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, on the Vulture’s Peak "
"Mountain, not long after Devadatta had left."

msgctxt "sn6.12:1.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho brahmā sahampati abhikkantāya rattiyā abhikkantavaṇṇo kevalakappaṃ "
"gijjhakūṭaṃ pabbataṃ obhāsetvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā "
"bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi."
msgstr ""
"Then, late at night, the beautiful Brahmā Sahampati, lighting up the entire "
"Vulture’s Peak, went up to the Buddha, bowed, stood to one side,"

msgctxt "sn6.12:1.4"
msgid ""
"Ekamantaṃ ṭhito kho brahmā sahampati devadattaṃ ārabbha bhagavato santike "
"imaṃ gāthaṃ abhāsi:"
msgstr "and recited this verse in the Buddha’s presence:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.333"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn6.12:2.1"
msgid "“Phalaṃ ve kadaliṃ hanti,"
msgstr "“The banana tree is destroyed by its own fruit,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn6.12:2.2"
msgid "phalaṃ veḷuṃ phalaṃ naḷaṃ;"
msgstr "as are the bamboo and the reed."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn6.12:2.3"
msgid "Sakkāro kāpurisaṃ hanti,"
msgstr "Honor destroys a sinner,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn6.12:2.4"
msgid "gabbho assatariṃ yathā”ti."
msgstr "as pregnancy destroys a mule.”"
